<b>Reading List</b>

For this ngVLA work there are a number of useful papers and memos that
everyone should be on top of. NB. all ngVLA memos can be found here:
http://library.nrao.edu/ngvla.shtml

The following are (what I think are!) the most relevant. Those
involved in this work should be on top of them. This list will get
added to.

1. ngVLA Astro 2020 Decadal Review White Paper
https://science.nrao.edu/science/astro2020/apc-white-papers/137-fe4771da409a7413465c9bb1cb579ae7_McKinnonMarkM.pdf

2. ngVLA Memo #73
Preliminary ngVLA Observing Band Availability Estimate
http://library.nrao.edu/public/memos/ngvla/NGVLA_73.pdf

3. ngVLA Memo #48
ngVLA Radio Frequency Interference Forecast
http://library.nrao.edu/public/memos/ngvla/NGVLA_48.pdf

4. Enriquez et al. 2017 paper
Contains tables and figures comparing past SETI projects
https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2017ApJ...849..104E/abstract

